{
  "answer": "**The figure of the cup-bearer (*saqi*, often rendered as \"Saqi,\" \"Cupbearer,\" or \"Cup-bearer\" in translations) is a prominent motif in classical Urdu ghazal poetry, symbolizing the beloved, divine grace, or the server of wine in mystical and romantic contexts.** It appears extensively in the following works from the corpus, primarily 19th- and 20th-century Urdu poetry collections:\n\n- **Diwan-E-Ghalib** by Mirza Ghalib (19th century): Numerous ghazals invoke the *saqi* as a figure of intoxicating beauty and reluctance, such as pleas for wine amid heartbreak.[^1][^2]\n- **Diwan-E-Zauq** by Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq (19th century): Features direct addresses to the *saqi* in humorous and desperate calls for wine, exemplifying courtly poetic tradition.[^3]\n- **Bang-E-Dara** by Allama Iqbal (1924; spans Parts 2 and 3 in the corpus): Uses the *saqi* metaphorically in modern nationalist and spiritual verses, critiquing eras or praising revelry.[^4][^5]\n\n**Incidental mentions of \"cup-bearer\" (not *saqi*) appear in Old English works like *Andreas* and *Old English Elegies*, but these refer to mead-hall servers in a Germanic heroic context, unrelated to the Persianate poetic figure.** No other works in the 37-work corpus engage the *saqi* motif substantively.\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/02-aabroo-kya-khaak-uss-gul-ki-ke-gulshan-mein-nahin/translation/#p-6cadea).\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/14-bahut-sahi-gham-e-geeti-sharaab-kam-kya-hai/translation/#p-74a1cf).\n[^3]: Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, *Diwan-E-Zauq*, [paragraph](/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/58-kahan-talak-kahoon-saqi-ke-laa-sharaab-to-de/translation/#p-8b86a8).\n[^4]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/05-zamana-aaya-hai-be-hijabi-ka-aam-deedaar-e-yaar-ho/translation/#p-445c2f).\n[^5]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/25-wataniyat/translation/#p-79b1e9).",
